about.inbox.intro1: You now see the new inbox and profile in Altinn. These will eventually replace today's solutions. The goal is to make it easier for you to find your way, keep an overview and have better dialogue with the public sector.
about.inbox.intro2: The new inbox is part of
about.inbox.section.availability.link: the inbox you are familiar with.
about.inbox.section.availability.p1: The new solution is being rolled out gradually, so some messages or functions may be missing. Until everything is in place, you can still use the version of the inbox and profile you are familiar with.
about.inbox.section.availability.title: Still under development
about.inbox.section.dialogs.p1: Altinn collects all digital communication with the public sector. In the new inbox, messages that belong to one dialogue are grouped, so you get a clearer picture. It is developed with a focus on making it simpler and more organized for you who have many messages. You can see the status of a case and whether it requires action, and it clearly shows when the dialogue was last updated, and who has read it. You can also move and sort what should be archived, and if you delete a dialogue by mistake, you can undo the deletion.
about.inbox.section.dialogs.title: This is new in the inbox
about.inbox.section.feedback.p1: We greatly appreciate input. If you have questions or suggestions, please send us an e-mail at
about.inbox.section.feedback.title: Please give us feedback
about.inbox.section.profile.p1: The new profile gives you a modern look with user-friendly navigation and simpler profile settings. You get a clearer overview of yourself, your favorites and businesses or associations you have access to. Notification settings can be controlled across all actors, and if you have access to several, it becomes easier to see which notifications apply to whom. More functions will be added over time, and we are working to gather everything in one place, so you get a full overview of whom you represent, and what roles and rights you have.
about.inbox.section.profile.title: This is new in the profile
